

LAMOG

   This word is often used in reference to fruit getting “beaten” or
   “bruised” up.

   If you place a whole piece of fruit like an apple in a very large empty
   can in the back of a truck, by the end of an hour-long drive over bad
   roads, that apple is going to be badly bruised.

MGA KAHULUGAN SA TAGALOG

   lamog: bugbog

   nalamog: nabugbog

   nalalamog: nabubugbog
